description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you take enormous pride in delivering safe, compassionate care, resulting in a high quality patient experience? If so we want you to join our committed, dynamic Dementia and Delirium Team at Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking to appoint a permanent full time Band 6 Registered Mental Health Nurse with recent experience of working in dementia care. We are looking for an outstanding candidate to provide person centered, quality care who is passionate about improving the care for people living with dementia and those caring for them. A good working knowledge around therapeutic and pharmacological management of behavioural and psychological symptoms of dementia is essential, alongside acute inpatient care. Experience of caring for patients affected by delirium is an advantage, however full training on delirium will be available.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To apply for this post you should be a highly motivated nurse who will work in accordance with local and national policy strategies to ensure that our patients have access to excellent care that is innovative, dynamic and of the highest professional standard. You will be able to demonstrate excellent communication/presentation skills and enjoy working as part of a team as teaching others and role modelling will form a significant part of your role. Autonomy, organisation and self-motivation are two key attributes we are looking for. The ability to lead a team and support junior staff members in the absence of the Dementia and Delirium Team Lead is essential.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post involves working within the trust and in the local community and therefore a car driver is essential. Job share or part time hours will be considered and you will be expected to work a flexible work pattern which may include weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The interview will include a short presentation on the following subject &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- What is the role of the Dementia and Delirium nurse and how your leadership style will support the ongoing development of the service.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust have now merged into the University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 24th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Katie Horswill&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Dementia and Delirium Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: katie.horswill@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0300 019 5512&lt;/p&gt;
